restaurant.name: Omakaseed
restaurant.description:
Omakaseed brings experiential dining and a unique flair for service to a vastly underserved market within the plant-based community. With a focus on Japanese-inspired vegan omakase, Omakaseed seeks to continue the mission of the team behind Sushi By Bou We focus on natural, minimally processed ingredients, highlighting seasonal and local produce. Omakaseed puts an emphasis on conscious cuisine and expanding the palettes of all who join us, vegan or not.

60-minute, 15 Course Vegan Omakase is $65++ per person. Beverages may be purchased at an additional cost. Please arrive a few minutes early.

Omakaseed 24-hour Cancellation Policy: A 50% per person fee will apply to cancellations and no-shows for reservations made within 24 hours of reservation time. Parties who arrive more than 10 minutes late can not be accommodated and will be subject to the no-show fee. Text 347-997-1615 to cancel your reservation within 24 hours of the reserved time. No phone calls, please!
restaurant.cateringDetails: Please email omakaseed@simplevenue.com with catering inquiries.

reviews.text: It was such a great experience! The server, Shin, was so skilled at preparing the meals and the whole vibe was very fun. Definitely going back!
Wonderful - this place was quick, but it was so much fun.
Food was great. Chef is very creative with omakase. We really enjoyed our meal. All 15 items were very good.
Food quality was mediocre at best, space/service was quite awkward and uncomfortable, but mainly just outlandishly overpriced for what you are getting.

reviews.text: Excellent food and presentation. Our server was really good and even gave us a free drink because we had a bit of a wait. I would encourage everyone to try this amazing place.

Omakaseed is an unusual restaurant - it's Japanese-focussed but with a touch of hip - in the service and decor.  The concept of having 8 people at the counter for a vegan Omakase meal individually prepared by two Sushi chefs is not novel in itself, but Omakaseed makes it fun and intimate.  Food was really innovative and tasty.  Good drink selection.  Highly recommend.

15 Course Omikase , No Meat, No Fish, purely Vegan dishes with an amazing amount of flavor and style brought to town! Loved it here! The chefs were awesome and fun, the Maitre’D was informative and accommodating. The Sake Flight was great as well! We’ll be back!
Omakaseed is revolutionizing sushi. Had an absolutely incredible meal and was blown away. Highly recommend for a great experience.
Definitely a great experience even for non vegetarian like myself, food looked and tasted amazing

I love regular sushi so was super intrigued to try the Omakase vegan sushi.  I was pleasantly surprised to find that the food was really innovative and delicious. Every single Nigiri piece was very well balanced in terms of flavor and the flow / order was great. 

The setting is fine -- not overly complicated and actually pretty casual. The experience is one hour, which definitely feels rushed as I'm not used to eating like this. I like to take my time and savor the flavors and that's not really possible with this style. 

Lastly,  I found the host incredibly rude and abrasive, which made for a lackluster experience.

Eh, cute concept but mediocrely executed. Waitstaff was bizarre and seemed untrained, reaching through us in distracting and frequent ways, interjecting often to tell us proper way of eating, chef was being trained in front of us , dessert was served before our last hand roll, felt rushed, seated us super late

reviews.text: In a shared space, so not as intimate as I had hoped. Very tasty!
The food was innovative and delicious. The staff were incredibly attentive.
A great experience all around. Delicious food. Friendly people.
Awesome Omakase experience!  The food was phenomenal and the wait staff were very attentive!  Highly recommend!  We will be going again!

Every dish had me questioning, is this really vegan? Never knew vegan food could be so unique, so flavorful, and so filling! Chef Roberto is charming and engaging, and will fill you in personally on each and every dish. Can't wait to go back!

LOVED the plant based sushi experience. And it was an experience!!! Chef was there to guide us through the influences, ingredients, and process behind each item. It was creative, exciting, and will inform my cooking moving forward. Everyone on the team was thoughtful and engaged in making sure we had a good experience.

For some constructive feedback, turn the music down about 20%? Its a personal plea of mine, I feel food/dining is a multisensory experience and find loud music pulls me away from concentrating on elements of the experience.
Amazing 15 course vegan sushi dinner. Honestly thought this was well priced compared to similar dining experiences in NYC. Everything was delicious and so unique.
Just incredible!
Omakaseed was such a fun and unique dining experience for vegans and nonvegans alike! I would definitely recommend it to everyone!
Delicious food but not a very relaxing meal. Only 75min for 15 courses …was not able to hear what i was being served or enjoy my food.
Fantastic vibe, friendly staff, delicious food. A simple, delightful experience that was well worth it.
